4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GRANTING THE DEPARTMENT OF FISH, WILDLIFE, AND
5 PARKS AUTHORITY TO MANAGE THE COLLECTING OF NATURALLY SHED ANTLERS AND HORNS OF
6 ELK, DEER, AND ANTELOPE AND THE ANTLERS OR HORNS OF A GAME ANIMAL, EXCEPT FOR
7 MOUNTAIN SHEEP, WITH A SKULL OR A PORTION OF A SKULL ATTACHED WITHIN THE STATE;
8 PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; IMPLEMENTING A WAITING PERIOD FOR NONRESIDENTS;
9 ESTABLISHING RESIDENT AND NONRESIDENT COLLECTING LICENSES; REVISING CRIMINAL ACTS
10 RELATED TO POSSESSING SHEDS; DEFINING "SHEDS"; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 87-1-201, 87-1-
11 304, 87-2-101, 87-2-106, 87-2-201, 87-2-202, 87-6-202, AND 87-6-206, MCA.”
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Class F-1--resident shed collecting license. (1) A resident as defined
16 in 87-2-102, on payment of a $10 fee, is entitled to receive a Class F-1 license that, except as provided in
17 subsection (2), authorizes the holder of the license to collect and possess naturally shed antlers and horns of
18 elk, deer, and antelope and the antlers or horns of a game animal, except for mountain sheep as provided in
19 87-3-315, with a skull or a portion of a skull attached that has died from natural causes and that has not been
20 unlawfully killed, captured, or taken or accidentally killed as prescribed by rules of the department.
21 (2) A license is not required by a landowner, their immediate family, or the landowner's employees
22 on the landowner's land for the collecting of naturally shed antlers and horns of elk, deer, and antelope or the
23 antlers or horns of a game animal, except for mountain sheep as provided in 87-3-315, with a skull or a portion
24 of a skull attached that has died from natural causes and that has not been unlawfully killed, captured, or taken
25 or accidentally killed.
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Class F-2--nonresident shed collecting license. (1) A person who is
28 not a resident as defined in 87-2-102, on payment of a $50 fee, is entitled to receive a Class F-2 license that,
